THAT
MINIMIZE
THE
HEATING
OF
THE
VEHICLES
WITHIN
ACCELERATION
OR
RANGE
CONSTRAINTS
A
NEW
METHOD
OF
NUMERICAL
SOLUTION
IS
USED
SIMILAR
TO
KELLEYS
METHOD
OF
GRADIENTS
THAT
PERMITS
RAPID
CONVERGENCE
TO
THE
OPTIMUM
LIFT
PROGRAM
STARTING
WITH
AN
ORIGINAL
GOOD
ESTIMATE
THIS
METHOD
AVOIDS
THE
TWOPOINT
BOUNDARYVALUE
PROBLEM
OF
THE
CALCULUSOFVARIATIONS
FORMULATION
AND
IS
APPLICABLE
TO
ANY
OPTIMUMPROGRAMING
